Describe a person who impressed you most when you were in primary school
- who he/she is
- how you know him/her
- why he/she impressed you most
- how you feel about him/her

I’d like to talk about my literature teacher, Ms. Anh, who left a lasting impression on me when I was in primary school.

I first met her when I was in grade 5. At that time, she was still quite young, probably in her mid-twenties, and relatively new to teaching. I remember being immediately impressed by her warm personality, gentle voice, and friendly smile, which made her very approachable to students.

What stood out the most, however, was her teaching style. Unlike many other teachers, she encouraged us to think creatively and express our own ideas instead of simply following a fixed interpretation. She often designed engaging activities that made her lessons more interactive and enjoyable. As a result, even though literature can be considered a difficult or less exciting subject by some students, her classes were always lively and full of energy.

I could clearly see her passion for teaching, as she put a lot of effort into every lesson. Thanks to her, I developed a genuine interest in literature, which I hadn’t had before. She not only helped me improve academically but also inspired me to think more deeply and creatively.

Even now, after many years, she remains one of the most memorable teachers I’ve ever had. I feel very grateful to have learned from her, and I truly admire her dedication and enthusiasm for teaching.
